<p>But I got a freaking Weller soldering iron, which cost more than the Axo boards I want to solder on <img src="../../images/emoji/twitter/slight_smileae52.png?v=5" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"> haha <img src="../../images/emoji/twitter/slight_smileae52.png?v=5" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"> So I got the right tools, I think. </p>

<p>But about my soldering skilles. Only think I really soldered was the Axo control board, which as you can read in my first description only lastet for a while, before it started failing, which resultet in humming on the output of Axoloti. </p>

<p>About the "low output issue":<br>The first badge of Axolotis had some issues that could cause the output to go almost mute.</p>

